Entry.JapaneseText: この街はずっと こんな調子さ
Entry.EnglishText: This village has a pretty depressing tone to it, doesn't it?

Entry.JapaneseText: こんなに貧しいのに、 ここの人々は何の見返りもなく 僕を受け容れてくれた
Entry.EnglishText: Everyone suffers through poverty. Each person gives me something to think about.

Entry.JapaneseText: 僕はエルフだ。 だが、魔術が使えない
Entry.EnglishText: You know I'm an Elf. But despite that I can't use magic.

Entry.JapaneseText: それって、 『レスネス』ってヤツ？ 前に本で読んだ
Entry.EnglishText: Does that mean you're a..."Lessneth"? I've read that in a book before

Entry.JapaneseText: 魔術使えないエルフ。 百年にひとりしか 生まれねんだって
Entry.EnglishText: They are Elves who can't use magic. One is born every 1000 years.

Entry.JapaneseText: 『レスネス』はエルフの里を 不幸にするとされていて、 生まれるとすぐ里を追い出される
Entry.EnglishText: In Elf village Lessneths are considered a sign of misfortune and sorrow. They're banished right after being born.

Entry.JapaneseText: じゃあ、 バジルさんも……
そう。居場所をなくした僕は この街に流れついた
Entry.EnglishText: Precisely. Without anywhere to go I wandered and ended up in this village.

Entry.JapaneseText: よそ者の僕にも ここの人たちはよくしてくれた
Entry.EnglishText: These people were used to strangers like me and understood me.

Entry.JapaneseText: だから、 アルヴァニスタじゃなくて ここに？
Entry.EnglishText: So that's why you stayed here and not in Alvanista?

Entry.JapaneseText: ああ。ここの方が 居心地がいいからね
Entry.EnglishText: Yes, I feel more comfortable around here. It's my true home.

Entry.JapaneseText: それに、一番大切なことを 教えられる気がするんだ。 自分が今、何をするべきか
Entry.EnglishText: More importantly, I think I've learned something priceless here. I want to help this place as much as I can.

Entry.JapaneseText: それが 魔術の研究？
Entry.EnglishText: I guess that's why you got into Magic Research.

Entry.JapaneseText: 人も『レスネス』も関係なく、 魔術を使えるようになるための 技術の研究さ
Entry.EnglishText: Both humans and Lessneths can relate in that they hope to find means to use magic.

Entry.JapaneseText: 魔術がもっとなじめば、 きっとこの村を、いや世界を もっと豊かにできるんだ
Entry.EnglishText: If we're able to achieve that, people will have new possibilities... No... the entire world will change!

Entry.JapaneseText: どんな大きな夢でも 思い続けなければ叶わない
Entry.EnglishText: No matter how big your dream is if your mind isn't set to see it through to the end you'll never make it a reality.

Entry.JapaneseText: 信じることが 大切なんだ
Entry.EnglishText: Believing is the most important part.

Entry.JapaneseText: 君には そういう夢はないのかい？
オレ……？ オレはええっと……
何かって…… きみは、もう……
じゃなくって！ どうすりゃいいかは わかんねーけど、自分の足で 歩いてけるようになりたいんだ
Entry.EnglishText: Stop that! I'm not entirely sure yet but... With one step at a time everyone can do anything!

Entry.JapaneseText: ハハッ、 ゆっくり考えればいいさ。 君の未来は真っ白だ
Entry.EnglishText: Haha! Think about it slowly. Your dream is as noble as it can get.

Entry.JapaneseText: 君はまだ どんなものにでも なれるんだからさ
Entry.EnglishText: You keep trying and you'll see you'll be able to do anything!

Entry.JapaneseText: 真っ白…… どんなもんにでも……
Entry.EnglishText: A noble dream... What do you mean...?

Entry.JapaneseText: 強く願い続ければ、 どんな気持ちでも叶う、 そう思うんだ
Entry.EnglishText: If your dream is strong your feelings will become true. Never forget your dream.

Entry.JapaneseText: だから、 がんばれよ、<DIO>！
僕も人を応援している場合じゃ ないんだけど
Entry.EnglishText: In my case not many people help me.

Entry.JapaneseText: でも、<KLA>もまた やる気になってくれたし、 研究も進展すると思う。
Entry.EnglishText: But knowing <KLA> is there I'm sure there'll always be progress.

Entry.JapaneseText: 魔科学があれば もう少し……
Entry.EnglishText: With a little more, Magitechnology will...
Rody, what are you doing over there?

Entry.JapaneseText: ん？ 空がきれいだなって 見とれてたんだ
Entry.EnglishText: W-what? I was taking some time to glance at the beauty of the sky.

Entry.JapaneseText: さてと……どこか 泊まれるところを 借りられないだろうか
Entry.EnglishText: Anyhow, we need to find a place to stay for the night.

Entry.JapaneseText: そうか、よかったら、 うちを使ってくれ
Entry.EnglishText: You're right. You can use this house over here.

Entry.JapaneseText: アルヴァニスタから 返信があったよ
それで、 ウンディーネんとこへ 行けんだな
Entry.EnglishText: Can we go to Undine's place now?

Entry.JapaneseText: ああ、北の海の<Red>浸食洞<White>の 立ち入り許可証だ
Entry.EnglishText: Yes. Travelling north you'll find Limestone Cavern.

Entry.JapaneseText: サンキュー、 バジルさん！
ありがとうございます
将来、君たちに目指すものが 見つかるよう応援しているからね
Entry.EnglishText: If you need any help in the future just ask me.

Entry.JapaneseText: <KLA>、 約束、忘れないでくれよ
うぉし、 <DIO>くん、<MEL>ちゃん、 精霊さんに会いに行こうぜ
Entry.EnglishText: All right! <DIO>, <MEL>! It's time to give the Spirit a visit it'll never forget!
